# FinTech & Innovation Internship - CommBank

## Role Description
CommBank's X15ventures and Innovation Labs are the bank's internal startup engines, building the next generation of financial products for Australian consumers and businesses. As a FinTech & Innovation intern, you'll work within an agile squad prototyping digital banking solutions, open banking integrations, and AI-driven financial tools.

## Key Responsibilities
* Contribute to the design and prototyping of new digital banking features within CommBank's app ecosystem
* Explore and evaluate emerging FinTech trends including embedded finance, BNPL, blockchain, and AI-driven lending
* Build proof-of-concept integrations using CommBank's open banking APIs (CDR-compliant) and third-party fintech partners
* Participate in innovation sprints and hackathons, presenting outcomes to the X15ventures investment committee

## Technical Skills & Requirements
* Comfortable with API integration and REST concepts; experience with Postman or similar tooling
* Basic coding ability in Python or JavaScript to prototype lightweight automation or integration scripts
* Understanding of open banking, Consumer Data Right (CDR), and Australia's fintech regulatory landscape
* Enrolled in FinTech, Computer Science, Business Information Systems, Finance, or related field (any year considered)

## Perks & Benefits
* Work from CommBank's innovation hub at Eveleigh, Sydney — a purpose-built tech and startup campus
* Access to X15ventures' network of Australian fintech startups and venture capital partners
* Innovation stipend of $500 AUD for purchasing tools, courses, or resources relevant to your project
* Fast-tracked consideration for CommBank's Technology Graduate Program
